{"id":"81a7fde0-fa3e-46d4-b1f1-d7df061f531a","title":"1555: To Messer Bartolomeo Ammannati","type":"main-list-block","children":[{"id":"c6410c06-7b76-4a7e-96c2-0d18e6640dd2","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"From Rome, [ ..., 1555]","standoffProperties":[{"id":"00a5a8f2-2fd1-407f-87c5-884b4da619cf","type":"text/sentence","start":0,"end":15,"value":"1","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"88b7266c-f34d-446f-bb79-d90056890b12","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":5,"end":8,"value":"501a8a32-2c8a-4934-9060-8c7e36339f0f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"f4e1b37f-c3db-4e8d-9962-18ed8f6b4678","type":"text/sentence","start":16,"end":23,"value":"2","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"bd7db6c6-d1d7-4fa9-b21d-7c0e619bc193","type":"codex/time-reference","start":18,"end":21,"value":"21a137be-b596-4157-a3b1-15ae1cf08545","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"94da448f-4aff-4d09-9c91-1d3f1cacaf9b","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"[To Messer Bartolomeo Ammannati.]","standoffProperties":[{"id":"c27926fd-9701-44c4-9836-451550fb5ee7","type":"text/sentence","start":0,"end":32,"value":"3","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"85751367-1235-4520-b226-24606c63beb2","type":"style/italics","start":1,"end":30,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"c056d22e-e4ef-4804-8da0-2c46113cde6a","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":4,"end":30,"value":"cadf2170-58b6-4e5b-be16-c081ebbf74fd","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[{"id":"c27926fd-9701-44c4-9836-451550fb5ee7","type":"text/sentence","value":"3","metadata":[]}]},{"id":"2c7ae28f-ae7f-410b-a629-60f8558f87da","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"","standoffProperties":[],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"1ce0299a-3ea1-4436-87e1-83ad3fc42ddf","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"Messer Bartolomeo, dear friend,\u00A0\u2014\u00A0It cannot be denied that Bramante was a skilful architect and the equal of any one from the time of the ancients until now. It was he who drew up the original plan of\u00A0St. Peter\u0027s, not full of confusion but clear and straightforward, with ample light and detached from the surrounding buildings so that it did not in any way interfere with the Palace. It was considered to be a fine design, and there is still evidence that it was so: indeed, every architect who has departed from Bramante\u0027s plan, as Sangallo has done, has departed from the right way, and that this is true may be seen by anybody who looks at his model with unprejudiced\u00A0eyes. In the first place, the outer ring of chapels he shows will exclude all the light provided by Bramante\u00A0in his plan; and not only this, but he has not provided any fresh means of lighting, while there are so many gloomy lurking-holes both above and below that any\u00A0sort of knavery could easily be practised, such as the\u00A0hiding of banished persons, the coining of false money, the rape of nuns, and other misdemeanours: and when at night the time comes for shutting up the church it would require twenty-five men to make\u00A0sure that no person remained there in hiding, and it\u00A0would be sufficiently difficult to find them. Furthermore, there would be this other drawback, that in\u00A0adding this circular work to the outside of Bramante\u0027s plan it would be necessary to pull down the Pauline\u00A0Chapel, the Offices of the Piombo, the Ruota, and many other buildings. I do not think that even the Sistine Chapel would remain intact. As to the\u00A0portion of the external ring which has already been\u00A0carried out, and which they say has cost a hundred\u00A0thousand crowns, this is not true, for it could be done\u00A0for sixteen thousand; and little would be lost if it\u00A0were pulled down, as the prepared stone and the foundations could not be more welcome, and would be worth two hundred thousand crowns and three hundred years of time to the building. This is my\u00A0opinion, expressed without prejudice, for to gain a victory in this matter would be to my very great loss. If you could let the Pope [Paul IV.] know what I think you would be doing me a service, as I do not\u00A0feel well enough to write myself.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"0aa66d0a-9622-4590-85ea-80471f8f2d78","type":"text/sentence","start":0,"end":156,"value":"4","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"2106c655-0e56-4a84-89de-3409099ce7d3","type":"salutation","start":0,"end":29,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"eb5b1321-79f4-4c6e-89d8-dd4605131edf","type":"style/uppercase","start":0,"end":29,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"d2ad2c1d-f886-4b2c-bc60-ce4f6bfc07ab","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":16,"value":"cadf2170-58b6-4e5b-be16-c081ebbf74fd","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"01e947fc-7a97-4f3d-9c1c-cae3f95a5309","type":"codex/meta-relation-reference","start":19,"end":29,"value":"fac7e7ec-6ac6-482f-a1e8-660b76fd9e5c","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"d5193c2c-0949-4b21-844a-1bffb5f8ea0e","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":59,"end":66,"value":"182beccf-0f45-466f-99a5-f0d510b042b2","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"ee36c73b-d2cf-43ca-a2e2-c01ea11cf946","type":"codex/trait-reference","start":74,"end":90,"value":"ed72f107-4e6d-402b-91a4-075d3af0e8c5","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"1a875d9d-e108-4b86-b4c5-9e74d27d1898","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":138,"end":145,"value":"bcf86523-1f72-413c-829b-8bc25631bbc7","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"aaca857f-9993-4b6f-87a8-9a98cac1b4ef","type":"text/sentence","start":157,"end":203,"value":"5","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"0540594a-9459-490a-9d0d-6289d0d868aa","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":165,"end":166,"value":"182beccf-0f45-466f-99a5-f0d510b042b2","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"cdf4c491-92c0-4f90-95ce-7d504ca31500","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":168,"end":170,"value":"182beccf-0f45-466f-99a5-f0d510b042b2","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"71577546-ab